CAIRO: Egyptian Ambassador Khaled Anis met with Malta’s prime minister to deliver an invitation to participate in the UN Climate Change Conference in Sharm El-Sheikh in November. Dr. Robert Abela expressed his gratitude for the invitation. During their meeting, Anis reviewed Egypt’s vision for the conference, from commitments to implementation. He also reviewed aspects of Egyptian-Maltese cooperation, including recent meetings on energy, water, air travel, trade and investment. Abela praised these developments and affirmed his support for the further strengthening of bilateral relations. He and Anis exchanged views on current global challenges, including the issues of energy, food security and rising prices.